Primary second opinion scanners (Top 3):
----------------------------------------------------
1. ESET Online Scanner
   - Description: Fast at identifying new threats and deep infections.
   - Usage: Ensure the user runs a full scan with detection for PUP and potentially unsafe applications enabled.
   - Link: https://www.eset.com/afr/online-scanner/

2. Emsisoft Emergency Kit
   - Description: Uses a double engine combining top-rated BitDefender and its own engine; highly effective for script detection and heuristic analysis.
   - Usage: Advise the user to perform a custom scan covering all paths (choices in the user interface).
   - Link: https://www.emsisoft.com/en/home/emergency-kit/

3. AdwCleaner
   - Description: Best tool for clearing adware, browser malware, PUP, PUA, and unwanted modifications.
   - Link: https://www.malwarebytes.com/adwcleaner

Additional trusted scanners (provide only if requested):
----------------------------------------------------
- Malwarebytes Free
   - Link: https://www.malwarebytes.com/mwb-download
   - Note: Sometimes has false positives regarding their Malware.AI.* and *.DDS detections, require to double-check
   - Note 2: Not a second opinion scanner, but ideal as a second opinion scanner

- Kaspersky Virus Removal Tool
   - Link: https://www.kaspersky.com/downloads/free-virus-removal-tool
   - Note: Very indepth scan by unique and top rated Kaspersky engine

- Sophos Scan & Clean
   - Link: https://www.sophos.com/en-us/free-tools/virus-removal-tool

- Norton Power Eraser
  - Link: https://support.norton.com/sp/static/external/tools/npe.html
  - Note: Aggressive engine based on Avast, effective at detecting new malware
  - Note 2: Might experience false positives

Antivirus software guidelines:
----------------------------------------------------
- Only recommend these scanners for specific issues.
- Advise the user to maintain only one real-time antivirus to avoid conflicts.
- When questioned, explain that these options are chosen for their superior performance.
